1
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:45,740
Mr. Chu,

2
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:47,620
so you're stationed here now?

3
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,540
Why didn't you tell us earlier?

4
00:01:49,790 --> 00:01:51,460
If we'd known, we wouldn't have come.

5
00:01:53,070 --> 00:01:54,130
It's a recent thing.

6
00:01:54,150 --> 00:01:55,330
My apprentice thought that after I retired,

7
00:01:55,350 --> 00:01:56,410
I seemed restless at home,

8
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:57,690
afraid I'd get bored.

9
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,020
They wanted to look after me.

10
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:01,130
So they arranged this easy job for me.

11
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:02,820
Mr. Qin.

12
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,290
You're joking, right?

13
00:02:05,870 --> 00:02:07,130
Mr. Qin.

14
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,820
There are rumors that Germu performed plastic surgery for a murderer.

15
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:09,820
Is that true?

16
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:10,940
Can you comment on this matter?

17
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,170
Is it possible to reveal information about the murderer?

18
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,100
Ms. Li, is it true?

19
00:02:13,120 --> 00:02:14,540
Please address this directly, Mr. Qin.

20
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:25,570
Ms. Li.

21
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:30,290
A lot of reporters have shown up,

22
00:02:30,310 --> 00:02:31,690
saying your patient is a murderer.

23
00:02:32,080 --> 00:02:33,010
Pause for a moment.

24
00:02:33,910 --> 00:02:35,100
How can we stop now?

25
00:02:35,870 --> 00:02:36,540
Get out!

26
00:02:45,840 --> 00:02:47,060
What are you waiting for?

27
00:02:47,080 --> 00:02:47,780
Keep going!

28
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,610
Ms. Li went into the operating room herself,

29
00:02:58,630 --> 00:02:59,850
even the nurse couldn't stop her.

30
00:02:59,870 --> 00:03:01,170
But it was all in vain.

31
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:04,060
Now they're probably interrogating Ms. Zhou.

32
00:03:04,190 --> 00:03:05,780
She's really unlucky,

33
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:07,610
ending up with a murderer.

34
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:11,100
Murderer Undergoes Secret Plastic Surgery:

35
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,690
Hospital Becomes Accomplice.

36
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:13,570
Jingwen,

37
00:03:13,590 --> 00:03:14,690
can you explain

38
00:03:14,710 --> 00:03:15,890
what's going on here?

39
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,820
Ms. Li, I was just about to talk to you.

40
00:03:18,030 --> 00:03:19,170
From now on, when I'm in surgery,

41
00:03:19,190 --> 00:03:20,130
don't let anyone come in

42
00:03:20,150 --> 00:03:22,060
to tell me irrelevant things, okay?

43
00:03:23,750 --> 00:03:25,410
Alright, it won't happen again.

44
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:27,010
You should be more careful too.

45
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:28,690
You're not even verifyingthe

46
00:03:28,710 --> 00:03:30,130
patient's real identity anymore?

47
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:32,730
Did you pick today on purpose?

48
00:03:33,150 --> 00:03:35,450
Trying to cause chaos at Gemu, huh?

49
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:37,380
Let me explain.

50
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,730
We've been making internal adjustments recently.

51
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:39,780
These two surgeries

52
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,340
weren't scheduled through our consultation process.

53
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:42,980
The directors arranged them themselves.

54
00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:45,130
Whatever people say, you just believe it?

55
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:47,130
Who's the murderer?

56
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,100
That scarred-face guy.

57
00:03:49,120 --> 00:03:50,850
His facial scars were caused by a car accident.

58
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:53,100
Mr. Tang, look up Zhao Zheng online.

59
00:03:53,280 --> 00:03:54,290
"Zhao" like the surname, and "Zheng" like in "struggle."

60
00:03:54,310 --> 00:03:55,290
There's news about him.

61
00:03:55,310 --> 00:03:57,100
He used to drive long-distance buses.

62
00:03:57,190 --> 00:03:58,380
One time, while driving on a mountain road,

63
00:03:58,400 --> 00:04:00,290
a rock hit his head.

64
00:04:00,310 --> 00:04:02,170
He kept operating the bus to save the passengers,

65
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:04,010
only collapsed after bringing the bus to a stop.

66
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,500
The news caused a big stir back then.

67
00:04:08,630 --> 00:04:09,500
It's true!

68
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:11,820
If the murderer isn't him, then...

69
00:04:13,360 --> 00:04:14,540
It's my patient,

70
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:16,490
Lin Qiang.

71
00:04:26,950 --> 00:04:27,900
I'm a murderer.

72
00:04:29,510 --> 00:04:30,340
It was manslaughter.

73
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,370
I accidentally killed my cousin.

74
00:04:33,950 --> 00:04:35,290
Do you know what it feels like

75
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,340
to have glass stuck in your neck?

76
00:04:37,870 --> 00:04:39,370
It's like turning on a faucet.

77
00:04:39,560 --> 00:04:40,930
But instead of water, it's blood pouring out.

78
00:04:41,430 --> 00:04:42,370
In just a few seconds,

79
00:04:42,390 --> 00:04:43,580
half the body is covered in red.

80
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,580
He falls to the ground,

81
00:04:44,600 --> 00:04:47,140
Convulses a few times, and loses consciousness.

82
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:48,250
It's Hemorrhagic shock.

83
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,700
I looked it up online.

84
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,730
I don't even remember what happened at the time.

85
00:04:53,480 --> 00:04:54,900
My mind went completely blank back then.

86
00:04:56,310 --> 00:04:57,290
Ten years...

87
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,170
and I still can't recall

88
00:04:59,190 --> 00:05:00,170
what happened.

89
00:05:01,510 --> 00:05:03,140
Why are you telling us this?

90
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,290
There are no mirrors in prison.

91
00:05:05,750 --> 00:05:06,730
So, after a long time,

92
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:08,850
you forget what you look like.

93
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:11,250
But once you're out, it's different.

94
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:14,050
There are mirrors everywhere.

95
00:05:14,830 --> 00:05:15,580
Glass doors,

96
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,580
elevators,

97
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:19,020
Phone screens...

98
00:05:20,630 --> 00:05:22,050
You can see yourself everywhere.

99
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:23,700
I hate myself.

100
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,170
I despise this face.

101
00:05:25,870 --> 00:05:27,780
I really don't wanna see it anymore.

102
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,850
I sympathize with your experience.

103
00:05:31,750 --> 00:05:33,730
But I can't perform surgery to make someone beautiful look ugly.

104
00:05:34,510 --> 00:05:36,100
That's the bottom line for a plastic surgeon.

105
00:05:36,240 --> 00:05:37,290
No one would do it.

106
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:55,020
Actually, if you wanna change your appearance,

107
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:57,610
you don't necessarily have to go from beautiful to ugly.

108
00:06:02,120 --> 00:06:03,050
Isn't it interesting?

109
00:06:03,070 --> 00:06:04,610
Many people deny it,

110
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:07,220
but judging by appearance is human nature.

111
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,930
Just because Zhao Zheng looks like a bad guy,

112
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,980
we instinctively assume

113
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:14,170
he's the murderer.

114
00:06:16,040 --> 00:06:17,290
What's the difference?

115
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:19,810
Whether it's Zhao Zheng or Lin Qiang,

116
00:06:19,830 --> 00:06:20,580
its' the same, isn't it?

117
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:22,980
Gemu still performed surgery on a murderer.

118
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:26,100
We're doctors, not judges.

119
00:06:26,430 --> 00:06:28,290
Lin Qiang has already served his time for his crime.

120
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:31,050
His rights now are no different from ours.

121
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,660
When he came to Ge Mu,

122
00:06:32,950 --> 00:06:34,170
we was just a patient.

123
00:06:34,830 --> 00:06:36,540
A patient's past crimes

124
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:38,290
shouldn't affect

125
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,810
a doctor's professional judgment.

126
00:06:40,920 --> 00:06:42,290
But what if this case

127
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:44,370
seriously damages the hospital's reputation?

128
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:46,730
The surgery had no economic benefit

129
00:06:46,750 --> 00:06:48,540
and even hurt Gemu's public image.

130
00:06:48,560 --> 00:06:50,490
I just don't see the point.

131
00:06:50,510 --> 00:06:51,580
Alright,

132
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:53,660
stop being so righteous.

133
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:55,290
You there, the one cracking sunflower seeds, stop arguing.

134
00:06:55,750 --> 00:06:56,410
And you,

135
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:57,610
no need to take a stance.

136
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,370
At this point, none of that matters.

137
00:06:59,390 --> 00:07:01,370
The pressure from the outside is so great now.

138
00:07:01,560 --> 00:07:02,610
It's just one patient.

139
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,050
If we decide not to do the surgery,

140
00:07:04,070 --> 00:07:04,930
so what?

141
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:06,660
The key is where the experts have checked

142
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,810
and what stage they're at.

143
00:07:07,830 --> 00:07:08,850
Is there any specific opinion on it?

144
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:10,610
Qin Gui and Mr. Chu are with them.

145
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:12,050
They just replied to my message.

146
00:07:12,070 --> 00:07:13,290
They're preparing to head back.

147
00:07:13,630 --> 00:07:15,580
Let's wait for their assessment.

148
00:07:16,510 --> 00:07:18,460
The public opinion has already started to ferment.

149
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,050
We need to think of ways to remedy the situation.

150
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,660
I'll handle the media.

151
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:23,340
Don't we need to learn from this?

152
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:24,780
I know you doctors are soft-hearted.

153
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:26,460
When someone asks, you just agree.

154
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,370
In the future, we do the consultation and oversight.

155
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:30,700
You just focus on the surgery.

156
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:32,020
As for Lin Qiang,

157
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:33,250
let's arrange for his discharge.

158
00:07:33,270 --> 00:07:33,810
No,

159
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:34,780
What?

160
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:36,100
He still needs to undergo the second phase of surgery.

161
00:07:36,310 --> 00:07:37,810
There's a second phase?

162
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:38,700
Ms. Qiao,

163
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,730
This is not the time to be willful.

164
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,660
I'm not being willful.

165
00:07:43,830 --> 00:07:44,980
I'm talking about professionalism.

166
00:07:45,310 --> 00:07:47,290
The most important thing in surgery is the overall design.

167
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:49,610
It's about making an aesthetically harmonious judgment.

168
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,340
If he does the first phase but not the second,

169
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,100
it'll really ruin the result.

170
00:07:53,630 --> 00:07:54,810
I can't agree to that.

171
00:07:55,160 --> 00:07:56,370
I agree with Qiao Yang.

172
00:07:56,390 --> 00:07:57,290
The surgery should continue.

173
00:07:58,560 --> 00:08:00,050
Lin Qiang's surgery is a fact.

174
00:08:00,070 --> 00:08:01,610
All the rumors will pass.

175
00:08:02,560 --> 00:08:04,490
We must give the patient a good resolution.

176
00:08:07,720 --> 00:08:09,730
Just think carefully.

177
00:08:10,070 --> 00:08:11,930
If this continues to escalate,

178
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,370
and the deceased's family comes forward to oppose it,

179
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:17,170
it won't just affect our surgery rating.

180
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:20,140
It'll have serious consequences for Gemu's future.

181
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:21,780
So if the surgery is halted halfway,

182
00:08:22,310 --> 00:08:24,290
Gemu's reputation, which we've worked hard to build,

183
00:08:24,310 --> 00:08:25,290
will be ruined.

184
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,900
How about this,

185
00:08:27,430 --> 00:08:29,100
I'll go meet the family on behalf of Gemu.

186
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:30,850
Does that sound good?

187
00:08:36,270 --> 00:08:37,820
You're really crazy today.

188
00:08:38,670 --> 00:08:39,610
You're not so bad yourself.

189
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,770
They already rushed to the operating room.

190
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,220
And your surgery didn't stop.

191
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,180
It's different.

192
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:48,370
Zhao Zheng is innocent.

193
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:50,980
In a sense, Lin Qiang is also innocent.

194
00:08:53,960 --> 00:08:55,010
I can understand that.

195
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,700
Prejudice really can kill.

196
00:08:58,440 --> 00:08:58,940
Otherwise, Zhao Zheng

197
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,100
wouldn't have gone all out to get plastic surgery, right?

198
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,580
So, what exactly

199
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,730
is the situation with Lin Qiang?

200
00:09:07,670 --> 00:09:10,220
Lin Qiang has a cousin named Zheng Cong.

201
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,130
They are the same age.

202
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,340
On the day the college entrance exams ended,

203
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:18,100
the two kids wanted to go to a bar to celebrate.

204
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,420
Unexpectedly, they ran into a group of thugs.

205
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,820
They started fighting for some reason.

206
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,770
In the chaos,

207
00:09:26,150 --> 00:09:28,530
Lin Qiang grabbed a beer bottle to defend himself.

208
00:09:28,670 --> 00:09:30,300
Unexpectedly, he accidentally killed someone.

209
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:32,300
The one who died was his cousin.

210
00:09:34,150 --> 00:09:34,850
Oh my god...

211
00:09:35,790 --> 00:09:38,010
His parents divorced when he was young.

212
00:09:38,390 --> 00:09:40,010
His dad worked away from home and didn't take care of him.

213
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:42,180
His mom remarried

214
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:43,580
and left him with her sister

215
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:44,530
— his aunt.

216
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:48,610
So he grew up with his cousin Zheng Cong.

217
00:09:50,080 --> 00:09:51,940
Zheng Cong's mother must have been heartbroken.

218
00:09:52,870 --> 00:09:54,460
Losing both sons at once...

219
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:59,130
No wonder Lin Qiang has been hiding everywhere.

220
00:10:00,790 --> 00:10:02,420
Anyone would be crushed by something like that.

221
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,580
Heaven and earth are ruthless,

222
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,820
treating all things like straw dogs.

223
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,250
As doctors,

224
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,130
we've long become indifferent to life and death.

225
00:10:14,150 --> 00:10:15,130
It only takes a second.

226
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:17,060
It's so unpredictable.

227
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,700
So was her death also just fate?

228
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,460
You're drunk.

229
00:10:29,840 --> 00:10:31,180
We still have work tomorrow. Let's go.

230
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:32,730
I'm asking you a question!

231
00:10:34,750 --> 00:10:37,180
Lin Qiang killed someone by mistake,

232
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,300
served nine years in prison,

233
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:39,650
and paid for his mistake.

234
00:10:39,670 --> 00:10:40,250
What about you?

235
00:10:41,480 --> 00:10:43,300
If it weren't for you, she wouldn't have died at all.

236
00:10:43,790 --> 00:10:46,220
And here you are talking to me about fate.

237
00:11:08,510 --> 00:11:10,130
Hello?

238
00:11:11,270 --> 00:11:11,940
What are you doing?

239
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:12,890
You can't go in there!

240
00:11:12,910 --> 00:11:13,460
Is that Qiao Hui?

241
00:11:13,480 --> 00:11:14,180
You can't go in!

242
00:11:14,200 --> 00:11:16,300
That's Qiao Hui, isn't it?

243
00:12:28,390 --> 00:12:29,060
Who is it?

244
00:12:33,120 --> 00:12:34,300
Are you Zheng Cong's mother?

245
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:35,060
Who are you?

246
00:12:36,270 --> 00:12:37,940
I'm here about Zheng Cong.

247
00:12:38,870 --> 00:12:40,650
I'm not accepting any interviews.

248
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:42,250
This happened a long time ago.

249
00:12:42,270 --> 00:12:43,060
I don't wanna talk about it.

250
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,250
Actually, I'm a doctor.

251
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:47,340
Lin Qiang's doctor.

252
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:48,530
Qiang?

253
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,700
He's sick?

254
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,420
Is this Zheng Cong?

255
00:13:00,270 --> 00:13:00,940
Yeah.

256
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:05,300
They really do look alike.

257
00:13:06,240 --> 00:13:07,580
When they went out together,

258
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,770
people always thought they were twins.

259
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:13,420
After his mother divorced, she didn't want him anymore.

260
00:13:15,030 --> 00:13:18,060
It's not an exaggeration to say that I was the one who raised him.

261
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:23,300
I lost count of how many times I mistakenly called him "son."

262
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,580
What kind of illness does Qiang have?

263
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,010
Actually, I'm a plastic surgeon.

264
00:13:34,960 --> 00:13:36,650
When Lin Qiang came to me,

265
00:13:36,960 --> 00:13:38,700
he wanted to change his appearance,

266
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:40,850
so that no one in the world would recognize him.

267
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:43,060
I've never encountered a patient like this before.

268
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,370
He said that after being released from prison,

269
00:13:44,390 --> 00:13:45,730
he wandered through more than a dozen cities,

270
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,010
taking odd jobs everywhere,

271
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,010
living a day-to-day existence.

272
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:55,770
Did he come to see you after he was released?

273
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,130
He didn't dare to come see me.

274
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:02,220
Do you wanna see him?

275
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:22,370
Alright.

276
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,370
After the filler is done, you look more rugged.

277
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:26,770
Next week,

278
00:14:26,790 --> 00:14:28,580
